-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/ukraine-s-agrarian-fund-purchases-860-000-metric-tons-of-grain.html
A state-run Ukrainian fund that
stockpiles farm products bought 860,000 metric tons of grain,
the  Agriculture Ministry  said.  The grain purchased by the Agrarian Fund via state-run
exporter Khlib Investbud is being harvested now, the Kiev-based
ministry said in an e-mailed statement today. The government
plans to spend 7.2 billion hryvnia ($900 million) to buy
agricultural commodities, it said.  The state will buy 1.05 million tons of wheat, 90,000 tons
of rye, 40,000 tons of barley and 30,000 tons of corn, according
to the statement. Sugar purchases will total 247,600 tons, it
shows.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 